photos.title: V-J Day in Times Square
photos.description: The V-J Day kiss in Times Square photo, taken by Alfred Eisenstaedt in 1945, captures an exuberant sailor spontaneously kissing a nurse amidst the celebrations of Japan's surrender, marking the end of World War II.

photos.title: Harvey Milk at San Francisco Gay Pride
photos.description: This photograph shows Harvey Milk, one of the first openly gay elected officials in the U.S., riding the San Francisco Gay Freedom Day Parade, symbolizing political progress for the LGBTQ+ community.

photos.title: Lesbian Couple at a San Francisco Pride Parade
photos.description: This image depicts a lesbian couple embracing during the pride parade in the lates 70s and reflects the visibility and solidarity within the LGBTQ+ community.

photos.title: John Lennon and Yoko Ono's Bed-In for Peace
photos.description: This photograph depicts John Lennon and Yoko Ono during their week-long Bed-In for Peace in Amsterdam, protesting against war and promoting peace.

photos.title: Muhammad Ali vs. Sonny Liston
photos.description: Photographed by Neil Leifer, this image captures Muhammad Ali standing over Sonny Liston after a first-round knockout, symbolizing Ali's cominance in boxing.

photos.title: Martin Luther King Jr.'s 'I Have a Dream' Speech
photos.description: The iconic photo of Martin Luther King Jr.'s 'I Have a Dream' speech shows him addressing a massive crowd at the 1963 March on Washington, symbolizing the fight for civil rights and racial equality in America.

photos.title: Lunch atop a Skyscraper
photos.description: This photograph captures 11 construction workers eating lunch on a steel beam, high above New York City during the construction of the RCA Building.

photos.title: Young couple relaxing during Woodstock Music Festival
photos.description: A young couple lies closely together on the grass during the Woodstock Music Festival, embodying the love, peace, and freedom that defined the iconic event.

photos.title: Eyes right
photos.description: Eyes right is executed with near-military precision by men aboard a New York-bound 20th Century Limited train as movie star Kim Novak eases into her seat in the dining car.

photos.title: Four lads from Liverpool
photos.description: Paul McCartney, George Harrison, John Lennon, and Ringo Starr â€” take a dip in an unheated Miami Beach swimming pool during a cold snap on their first trip to the States.

photos.title: Mickey Mantle flings helmet
photos.description: In one of the most eloquent photographs ever made of a great athlete in decline, Yankee star Mickey Mantle flings his batting helmet away in disgust after another terrible at-bat near the end of his storied, injury-plagued career.
